  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 350&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Slice&nbsp;the <strong>courgette</strong> in half&nbsp;lengthways and then into bite-size pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add them to a baking tray, drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong>, season&nbsp;with a pinch of both&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and put them in the oven for 15 min or until they've softened slightly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>peel and finely dice the <strong>red&nbsp;</strong><strong>onion</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>tomatoes</strong> into wedges</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil&nbsp;</strong>over a medium-high heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced</strong>&nbsp;<strong>onion</strong> and cook for 4 min or until it's softened slightly&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add half of the&nbsp;<strong>garlic</strong>&nbsp;(keep the rest for later) and <strong>chilli</strong> <strong>flakes</strong>&nbsp;(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for a further 1 min until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/793.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>Shaoxing</strong><strong>&nbsp;wine</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 sec or until it evaporates</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>tomatoes</strong>&nbsp;with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4 min until the tomatoes start to break down</p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium, add the <strong>king</strong>&nbsp;<strong>prawns</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 3 min or until they've turned pink</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
